             <h1>Chocolate Souffle</h1>
 <img src="https://bigoven-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/t_recipe-1280/chocolate-souffle-cakes-2.jpg" style="float:right;height:500px" />
 <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
 <h3>
     -100g dark chocolate
     <br />
     -100g butter
     <br />
     -1/2 cup/100g white sugar
     <br />
     -2 eggs
     <br />
     -2 egg yolks
     <br />
     45g/5 tablespoons white flour
     <br />
     -4 chocolate cubes
     <br />
     -canola/vegetable oil to coat the dishes
 </h3>
 <h2>Instructions:</h2>
 <h3>
     -Heat the oven to 180 degrees. Lightly coat the indidual dishes with the oil and place on a baking sheet.
     <br />
     -Melt the chocolate and butter in the microwave. Add the sugar and whisk to combine. Add the eggs and yolks and whisk to combine.
     <br />
     -Whisk in the flour until there are no lumps.
     <br />
     -Pour the batter into the individual dishes. drop the chocolate cubes into the batter in the dishes.
     <br />
     -Bake for about 15 minutes until the edges of the souffle are firm and the center is still soft.
     <br />
     -Cool for 2 minutes. Serve hot.
 </h3>
 
</asp:Content>
